# microCMS Configuration
# Replace with your actual microCMS service domain and API key
REACT_APP_MICROCMS_SERVICE_DOMAIN=your-service-domain
REACT_APP_MICROCMS_API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# Example:
# REACT_APP_MICROCMS_SERVICE_DOMAIN=foodie-delight
# REACT_APP_MICROCMS_API_KEY=abcd1234-efgh5678-ijkl9012-mnop3456

# Instructions:
# 1. Create a microCMS account at https://microcms.io/
# 2. Create a new service and note your service domain
# 3. Create the following APIs in your microCMS service:
#    - restaurants (with fields: name, description, category, rating, deliveryTime, deliveryFee, image, featured, address, phone, tags, openingHours)
#    - menu-items (with fields: name, description, price, category, restaurant, image, popular, dietary, ingredients, nutritionInfo)
#    - categories (with fields: name, description, icon, image, color, sortOrder)
# 4. Generate an API key in your microCMS service settings
# 5. Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
